title: Holy shazbat! I ...
content:
Holy shazbat! I thought I was the only one who was terrified of balloons! 
Or, perhaps it's a fear of the sound of latex products breaking...
As a Panphobic, I thought I would have trouble viewing "A Terrible Fear of 
Everything", but it wasn't so bad. Once I had made a fort out of the sofa 
cushions and blankets, and had plenty of flashlights, and my trusty light 
saber, and got my mom to check under all the beds and in the closets for 
monsters, and then push the play button on Netflix for me it was easy! 
After another month of therapy, and a larger dose of Valium, I'm hoping to 
see ALL of the opening credits. The trick is never to eat popcorn during 
scary movies. Monsters can smell it on you! <U+FEFF>

title: I have Generalized ...
content:
I have Generalized Anxiety Disorder, I fear most things, especially new 
things.  And since I have extremely sensitive skin, and when I was younger 
being in direct sunlight actually made me feel like my skin was on fire, I 
also get anxious about going in the sun, and refuse to go to water parks 
etc, ever.

I also have Ablutophobia, I hate bathing/cleaning, or being wet in general 
(swimming, playing in the rain, etc).  Most of this is attributed to being 
a co-morbid of the extreme sensitivities I suffer from due to my Autism 
Spectrum Disorder (high functioning).

Oh and in answer to your question, yes, I am afraid of the fear of 
everything because I'm constantly wondering if I am letting it run my life, 
and if I am, why can't I tell?

The mind is a crazy thing.


Oh and for those wondering, even though it takes an extreme act of personal 
courage just to get out of bed and out the door in the morning, I do have a 
successful career, my own place, and a loving wife.  It's all about how you 
deal!<U+FEFF>

title: The only phobia I ...
content:
The only phobia I have is arachnophobia (fear of spiders) because spiders 
are freaking creepy. If I see one, I'll be like "Meh" but I'll still panic 
a little bit. If a spider was on me or crawling up my arm or something like 
that, I would kind of freak out. I would either just stare with a look of 
panic (Something I do when I'm scared. It's normal.) or swat it away as 
fast as possible. Now, NIGHTMARES about spiders... That's another story. I 
FREAK OUT if I have a nightmare about evil spiders. Once I had some 
nightmare about a boy who went on a little adventure with his grandfather 
(it was basically just like Ib, but with little spiders everywhere). At the 
end they were in their beds saying goodnight. Then the boy's dad came in as 
a giant spider with human legs (I dunno but I think they were black and 
hairy like spiders are) and he went to the boy's bed. The boy couldn't see 
that his dad was a spider because the light was off and it was dark. The 
dad just said "Good night..." before he killed the boy and ate him. THAT'S 
WHY SPIDERS ARE SO SCARY TO ME! Oh, and also my mom has a bad case of 
chiroptophobia. Fear of bats. She HATES bats...<U+FEFF>
